result.execSummary:
The defendant Shaun M Kirchner was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Repeater, Use of a Dangerous Weapon], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Repeater, Use of a Dangerous Weapon], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant is NOT eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.  Defendant IS eligible for the Substance Abuse Program.

miscConds.notes: Maintain absolute sobriety. No use or possession of alcohol or illegal drugs/drug paraphernalia. All prescriptions to be filled at the same pharmacy.  Inform Agent of all prescriptions.

Engage in current Mental Health treatment.  Maintain current programs and develop new ones as needed for Mental Health.

Defendant is not to possess any dangerous weapons.  Maintain a valid drivers license.  Operate a motor vehicle only with a valid drivers license.  Comply with all orders of courts with competent jurisdiction.  No new law violations.  

Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

If probation is revoked and a prison term is not ordered, or if probation is discharged/terminated, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and government entities for outstanding financial obligations.  Collection may include income assignment.
Costs to be paid as a condition of probation within the first 18 months of probation.
